cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper discusses visual saliency models, which are primarily used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses cognitive studies of attention, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current models and the need for more powerful models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
